00:08:31.690 --> 00:08:35.060
How intellectual property, at
the time when I was growing up,

00:08:35.060 --> 00:08:37.140
had no idea of what
that even stood for,

00:08:37.140 --> 00:08:41.280
would not even have comprehended
what intellectual property would

00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:43.550
mean to me because if
somebody were to tell me,

00:08:43.550 --> 00:08:45.560
I wouldn't have recognized
it in its form.

00:08:45.560 --> 00:08:48.660
In fact, one of the things that
I'll challenge us here today

00:08:48.660 --> 00:08:52.980 position:56%
on World IP Day is to begin to think
differently on how we discuss IP,

00:08:52.980 --> 00:08:57.890
intellectual property, copyright,
patent, we go down the list.

00:08:57.890 --> 00:09:00.970
If it was important enough
to involve the Constitution

00:09:00.970 --> 00:09:03.590
of the United States, it should
be important enough for us today

00:09:03.590 --> 00:09:07.260
to be able to explain it in
very simple terms to everyone

00:09:07.260 --> 00:09:09.520
in our country on why
this is important

00:09:09.520 --> 00:09:13.820
and why copyright protection
is valuable to the economy

00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:18.760
of not only our financial sector
but it is valuable to the economy

00:09:18.760 --> 00:09:24.210
of the soul, because I was a kid
who grew up in northeast Georgia,

00:09:24.210 --> 00:09:25.510
a beautiful part of the world.

00:09:25.510 --> 00:09:27.560 position:56%
I'd encourage anyone to come and
especially if you're making a movie,

00:09:27.560 --> 00:09:31.330
we have a lot of places for
you to come and if you listen

00:09:31.330 --> 00:09:32.940
