00:10:00.040 --> 00:10:02.000
So for me, when I thought of
intellectual property at a time

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:04.700
which I did not, I just
thought of the things that I,

00:10:04.700 --> 00:10:07.910
besides being in the woods, and
being in the fishing, and lake

00:10:07.910 --> 00:10:10.190
and doing things, I would
come back to my room

00:10:10.190 --> 00:10:14.890
and I would have my music,
and I would have my books.

00:10:14.890 --> 00:10:18.260
It was once said that no person
could ever be bound to anywhere

00:10:18.260 --> 00:10:23.380 position:56%
as long as there was a book in their
hand and for me, that was true.

00:10:23.380 --> 00:10:26.810
For listening to a song that could
take me from the room in my house,

00:10:26.810 --> 00:10:29.000
or my back porch, or
standing in the front yard,

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:32.130
imitating that I was
performing for millions of people

00:10:32.130 --> 00:10:35.390
at a worldwide stage, it was
something inside of me although

00:10:35.390 --> 00:10:39.020 position:56%
for me who could not sing very well,

00:10:39.020 --> 00:10:43.690
the words still took me
away to a different place.

00:10:43.690 --> 00:10:50.070
